1
00:00:39,400 --> 00:00:42,067
<i>Mom, please. Take back
what you said to Uncle Noah.</i>

2
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,967
<i>This is my life.
I'm the one who gets to decide.</i>

3
00:00:44,100 --> 00:00:45,033
<i> You need to respect that!</i>

4
00:00:45,167 --> 00:00:47,300
<i>You keep saying
your ex has nothing to do</i>

5
00:00:47,433 --> 00:00:48,600
<i>with your sudden decision
to call off the wedding.</i>

6
00:00:48,733 --> 00:00:50,400
<i>Then why are you only changing
your mind now,</i>

7
00:00:50,533 --> 00:00:52,300
<i>right after something happened
to that guy in Canada?</i>

8
00:00:52,433 --> 00:00:54,133
<i>I've always cared
for this family.</i>

9
00:00:54,267 --> 00:00:55,967
<i>I'm the breadwinner.
It's all me!</i>

10
00:00:56,100 --> 00:00:58,633
<i>Dad may not earn a lot,
but he's still tried, Mom.</i>

11
00:00:58,767 --> 00:01:00,100
<i> He never laid a hand on me.</i>

12
00:01:00,233 --> 00:01:02,833
<i>So, don't be surprised
that my loyalty is with him!</i>

13
00:01:02,967 --> 00:01:05,633
<i>I never wanted to hurt you.
But why are you like this?</i>

14
00:01:05,767 --> 00:01:06,733
<i>Can't you see
we're talking here?</i>

15
00:01:06,900 --> 00:01:07,700
<i> And this is my daughter.</i>

16
00:01:07,833 --> 00:01:08,900
<i> I'm not yet done!</i>

17
00:01:09,033 --> 00:01:10,967
<i>What if dad tries to get back
together with you?</i>

18
00:01:11,100 --> 00:01:11,933
<i> That's never going to happen.</i>

19
00:01:12,067 --> 00:01:13,333
<i>He's already married
to that Hazel.</i>

20
00:01:13,467 --> 00:01:16,233
<i>Manuel's starting to get
on my nerves, seriously!</i>

21
00:01:16,367 --> 00:01:19,900
<i>Because he's the root cause
of all of this!</i>

22
00:01:20,033 --> 00:01:21,200
<i> Even if they break up,</i>

23
00:01:21,333 --> 00:01:23,000
<i>I have no intention of getting
back together with him.</i>

24
00:01:23,133 --> 00:01:25,967
<i>You're in denial. You still love
Manuel, don't you?</i>

25
00:01:26,100 --> 00:01:27,733
<i>I don't love
your father anymore.</i>

26
00:01:27,867 --> 00:01:29,867
<i> The administrator spoke to me.</i>

27
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:31,467
<i>Apparently, the patients here
have already filed a petition</i>

28
00:01:31,600 --> 00:01:32,400
<i> to have me removed.</i>

29
00:01:32,533 --> 00:01:33,767
<i> What are you doing here?</i>

30
00:01:33,900 --> 00:01:35,800
<i>- We're just following orders.
- No. I said take him back!</i>

31
00:01:35,933 --> 00:01:36,800
<i>- I don't want him here!
- Mom!</i>

32
00:01:36,933 --> 00:01:38,033
<i>- Stop it!
- Stop it!</i>

33
00:01:38,167 --> 00:01:39,200
<i> Felma!</i>

34
00:01:39,333 --> 00:01:41,467
<i>- Felma, can we talk, please?
- You're drunk.</i>

35
00:01:41,633 --> 00:01:42,433
<i> You should go home.</i>

36
00:01:42,567 --> 00:01:43,767
<i> Felma, I love you so much.</i>

37
00:01:43,900 --> 00:01:45,033
<i>Please, Felma.
I love you so much.</i>

38
00:01:45,167 --> 00:01:46,367
<i> Stop it, you're drunk!</i>

39
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:48,333
<i> Let go of me!</i>

40
00:01:48,467 --> 00:01:49,633
Let go of me!

41
00:01:49,767 --> 00:01:50,467
Uncle!

42
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,567
Uncle!

43
00:01:54,400 --> 00:01:55,267
Mom.

44
00:01:58,933 --> 00:02:00,767
Get out of here!

45
00:02:00,900 --> 00:02:02,967
- Felma, I'm sorry.
- Uncle, let's go!

46
00:02:03,100 --> 00:02:04,067
Leave!

47
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,333
- Let's go!
- Please, please!

48
00:02:05,467 --> 00:02:08,767
- Leave!
- Please, please!

49
00:02:08,900 --> 00:02:10,400
<i> Get lost!</i>

50
00:02:10,533 --> 00:02:12,400
Leave!

51
00:02:12,533 --> 00:02:16,100
- Felma, I'm sorry.
- Leave!

52
00:02:16,267 --> 00:02:18,067
- You should go, Uncle!
- Jeff! Jeff, wait!

53
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:20,933
- I need to talk to your mom!
- Uncle, not now.

54
00:02:21,067 --> 00:02:22,467
- Please.
- Please, Felma.

55
00:02:22,600 --> 00:02:24,433
- Jeff, let's go back inside.
- Let's go.

56
00:02:24,567 --> 00:02:26,200
I need to speak with your mom!

57
00:02:26,333 --> 00:02:27,600
Mom!

58
00:02:44,100 --> 00:02:46,467
Jeff, I need to apologize.

59
00:02:46,600 --> 00:02:48,333
I didn't mean to do that.

60
00:02:48,500 --> 00:02:50,733
You know how much I love
and respect your mom.

61
00:02:50,867 --> 00:02:51,833
- Jeff, please!
- Uncle, you call that respect?

62
00:02:51,967 --> 00:02:53,000
You're actually making
sexual advances on her!

63
00:02:53,133 --> 00:02:56,200
I regret it, Jeff!

64
00:02:56,333 --> 00:02:58,733
Jeff, I need to go inside,
please.

65
00:02:58,867 --> 00:03:00,733
I'm begging you, Jeff.

66
00:03:00,867 --> 00:03:04,167
I just can't accept
that your mom's leaving me.

67
00:03:04,300 --> 00:03:07,567
And, she just suddenly
doesn't want me anymore.

68
00:03:07,700 --> 00:03:08,867
Jeff, please.

69
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,467
I want to apologize to her.

70
00:03:10,600 --> 00:03:11,900
Uncle, not now.

71
00:03:12,033 --> 00:03:13,400
Mom will just get angrier.

72
00:03:14,467 --> 00:03:15,733
Let it cool down first.

73
00:03:15,867 --> 00:03:17,300
All right, please go home
for now.

74
00:03:17,433 --> 00:03:18,267
Jeff.

75
00:03:18,400 --> 00:03:19,567
Uncle, please listen.

76
00:03:21,467 --> 00:03:23,300
Let me take you home.

77
00:03:23,433 --> 00:03:24,067
Felma.

78
00:03:24,200 --> 00:03:25,433
I need to apologize, Jeff.

79
00:03:25,567 --> 00:03:26,800
Do it next time.

80
00:03:26,933 --> 00:03:28,533
I need to talk to Felma.

81
00:03:34,367 --> 00:03:35,833
He took advantage of me.

82
00:03:38,033 --> 00:03:41,233
Mom, we know Uncle Noah.

83
00:03:41,367 --> 00:03:43,267
He wouldn't do that.

84
00:03:43,400 --> 00:03:44,800
He was just drunk, that's why...

85
00:03:44,933 --> 00:03:47,100
Andrea, that's not an excuse.

86
00:03:48,633 --> 00:03:50,633
We know that, Coleen.

87
00:03:50,767 --> 00:03:53,400
But we also have to understand
his feelings.

88
00:03:54,500 --> 00:03:57,300
He couldn't handle it,
that's why he got drunk.

89
00:03:59,267 --> 00:04:00,433
That's not the point.

90
00:04:01,400 --> 00:04:06,600
The real issue
is that he came here drunk.

91
00:04:06,733 --> 00:04:09,100
And then he expects me...

92
00:04:09,233 --> 00:04:11,467
to talk to him?

93
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:15,700
Mom, I'm not trying
to defend Uncle Noah.

94
00:04:15,833 --> 00:04:18,467
But the person was hurt.

95
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,233
Mom...

96
00:04:20,367 --> 00:04:22,333
she has a point.

97
00:04:22,467 --> 00:04:24,067
All right, I'll let this go.

98
00:04:25,467 --> 00:04:27,000
But what he did to me...

99
00:04:28,733 --> 00:04:30,867
just pushed me
further away from him.

100
00:04:32,133 --> 00:04:34,833
Mom, weren't you the one
who first pushed him away?

101
00:04:41,333 --> 00:04:42,933
It's really my fault?

102
00:04:45,000 --> 00:04:46,033
Fine,

103
00:04:46,167 --> 00:04:49,067
let's say I was wrong.

104
00:04:49,200 --> 00:04:51,333
Because I gave him false hope.

105
00:04:51,467 --> 00:04:52,900
And maybe I shouldn't have
accepted his feelings.

106
00:04:53,033 --> 00:04:54,933
Maybe I shouldn't have.

107
00:04:55,067 --> 00:04:57,933
But don't I have the right
to make mistakes?

108
00:04:59,833 --> 00:05:02,167
Why can't you understand?

109
00:05:02,333 --> 00:05:04,367
Why can't you understand
my decision?

110
00:05:04,500 --> 00:05:06,700
It's easy to understand

111
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:09,467
if the man who left you
wasn't involved.

112
00:05:09,600 --> 00:05:10,733
Manuel again?

113
00:05:10,867 --> 00:05:11,367
- Yes!
- Still him?

114
00:05:11,500 --> 00:05:12,933
Yes, Mom!

115
00:05:13,067 --> 00:05:14,367
It's still him!

116
00:05:14,500 --> 00:05:16,333
Because if you had left
Uncle Noah

117
00:05:16,467 --> 00:05:19,633
before you even started
communicating with that man,

118
00:05:19,767 --> 00:05:21,300
we wouldn't be questioning you.

119
00:05:21,433 --> 00:05:22,733
Andrea, what's wrong with you?

120
00:05:22,867 --> 00:05:23,867
Why are you insisting

121
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:26,733
that dad had something to do
with mom's decision?

122
00:05:26,867 --> 00:05:29,000
Because that's what I see,
Coleen!

123
00:05:29,133 --> 00:05:30,133
Jeffrey and I see it!

124
00:05:31,200 --> 00:05:34,500
That man's been out of our lives
for 18 years.

125
00:05:34,667 --> 00:05:36,400
He's not here anymore.

126
00:05:36,533 --> 00:05:40,800
But we still can't find peace,
no matter what we do to move on.

127
00:05:42,133 --> 00:05:44,367
He still manages to get
in the way of our lives.

128
00:05:46,033 --> 00:05:47,267
I'm so fed up!

129
00:06:24,667 --> 00:06:26,700
I feel sorry for you, Dad.

130
00:06:26,833 --> 00:06:29,400
You're being blamed
for mom's decision.

131
00:06:30,367 --> 00:06:31,300
Coleen?

132
00:06:32,333 --> 00:06:34,267
Let me just get your laundry,
okay?

133
00:06:40,400 --> 00:06:41,167
Coleen?

134
00:06:42,167 --> 00:06:45,667
So you actually made an album
out of those pictures?

135
00:06:45,800 --> 00:06:48,167
But didn't you just take
those photos last week

136
00:06:48,300 --> 00:06:49,733
so that you'd have...

137
00:06:49,867 --> 00:06:51,033
what do you call it?

138
00:06:51,167 --> 00:06:53,200
A soft copy?

139
00:06:53,333 --> 00:06:55,000
And now this?

140
00:06:55,133 --> 00:06:56,400
Oh no.

141
00:06:56,533 --> 00:07:00,067
This is going to be an issue
when your siblings see it.

142
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:04,833
This is just for me, Didang.

143
00:07:04,967 --> 00:07:06,967
I won't show it to them.

144
00:07:08,500 --> 00:07:10,333
Make sure of that, Coleen.

145
00:07:11,900 --> 00:07:13,867
That will only cause
more trouble.

146
00:07:14,000 --> 00:07:18,433
Your dad's always the reason
for the fights around here.

147
00:07:18,600 --> 00:07:21,067
I feel sorry for Ma'am Felma.

148
00:07:22,100 --> 00:07:23,733
Like last night, for example.

149
00:07:23,867 --> 00:07:26,967
She and your sister Andrea
fought again.

150
00:07:27,100 --> 00:07:28,433
This kid!

151
00:07:38,267 --> 00:07:39,233
Dad.

152
00:07:40,867 --> 00:07:44,233
Even Didang blames you.

153
00:07:44,367 --> 00:07:46,133
You're never here.

154
00:07:47,200 --> 00:07:48,833
I wonder how you're doing.

155
00:07:52,033 --> 00:07:53,100
Coleen.

156
00:08:11,100 --> 00:08:12,467
Hello?

157
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,633
<i> Jessica?</i>

158
00:08:13,767 --> 00:08:15,500
Can I talk to dad?

159
00:08:19,833 --> 00:08:22,333
You've got some nerve calling
my child and my husband.

160
00:08:22,500 --> 00:08:25,700
You really take after
your worthless mother.

161
00:08:25,833 --> 00:08:29,167
Why? Did your mistress-mom
send you to mess up my family?

162
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:30,567
That's Coleen!

163
00:08:31,867 --> 00:08:33,767
- Mom, give it back to me!
- No!

164
00:08:33,900 --> 00:08:35,300
<i>- Give that back to her!
- Mom, give it back to me!</i>

165
00:08:35,433 --> 00:08:37,567
I won't let this girl
talk to you!

166
00:08:37,700 --> 00:08:39,600
Hey! From now on, don't ever try
calling here.

167
00:08:39,733 --> 00:08:40,567
Dad!

168
00:08:40,700 --> 00:08:42,333
Hazel, Hazel!

169
00:08:44,700 --> 00:08:45,433
Hello?

170
00:08:45,567 --> 00:08:46,500
What's going on?

171
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:49,433
Dad?

172
00:08:49,967 --> 00:08:50,467
Dad!

173
00:08:50,633 --> 00:08:52,600
<i> Dad! Dad, get up!</i>

174
00:08:52,733 --> 00:08:53,800
<i> Hazel, give me the phone!</i>

175
00:08:53,933 --> 00:08:56,600
What are you doing to my dad?

176
00:08:56,767 --> 00:08:59,100
Didn't I tell you not to talk

177
00:08:59,233 --> 00:09:00,733
to your mistress and your
illegitimate children,

178
00:09:00,867 --> 00:09:02,767
but you didn't listen!

179
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:05,733
Please stop!

180
00:09:05,867 --> 00:09:09,333
- Didn't I tell you?
- Dad!

181
00:09:09,467 --> 00:09:13,433
Don't hurt dad! Please stop!

182
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:17,000
Stop hurting Jessica!

183
00:09:17,133 --> 00:09:21,933
Please, I'm begging you!
Stop! Please stop!

184
00:09:22,067 --> 00:09:24,300
- You are worthless!
- Dad!

185
00:09:24,433 --> 00:09:28,033
I took you into this house
even when you were of no use!

186
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:29,767
But you still had the nerve
to disrespect me?

187
00:09:29,900 --> 00:09:31,533
You still managed
to do this to me?

188
00:09:31,667 --> 00:09:32,900
You're so shameless!

189
00:09:33,033 --> 00:09:35,500
So, so shameless!

190
00:09:35,633 --> 00:09:37,467
Mom, I'm begging you!

191
00:09:38,667 --> 00:09:39,767
Shut up!

192
00:09:39,900 --> 00:09:41,133
You two, be together!

193
00:09:44,867 --> 00:09:46,000
Hello!

194
00:09:46,133 --> 00:09:48,067
Hello!

195
00:09:50,467 --> 00:09:52,900
Dad!

196
00:09:53,033 --> 00:09:54,267
Are you okay?

197
00:10:00,800 --> 00:10:03,367
<i>That's exactly
what I was talking about!</i>

198
00:10:03,533 --> 00:10:06,300
So stop communicating
with your father.

199
00:10:08,067 --> 00:10:11,133
Mom, I'm just concerned
about dad's condition.

200
00:10:18,567 --> 00:10:19,567
That's enough.

201
00:10:20,767 --> 00:10:23,533
Forget what that witch
Hazel said.

202
00:10:23,667 --> 00:10:25,133
Dear.

203
00:10:25,267 --> 00:10:27,433
Dear, don't let it get to you,
okay?

204
00:10:27,567 --> 00:10:28,467
Stop crying.

205
00:10:28,600 --> 00:10:30,667
Ma'am, do you need me
to do anything else?

206
00:10:30,800 --> 00:10:32,600
I'll go downstairs for a bit.

207
00:10:33,867 --> 00:10:35,133
Didang,

208
00:10:35,300 --> 00:10:37,700
don't you ever tell
Jeffrey and Andrea

209
00:10:37,833 --> 00:10:39,533
about what happened, okay?

210
00:10:39,667 --> 00:10:41,167
Oh, of course not, Ma'am Felma.

211
00:10:41,300 --> 00:10:42,667
You know me.

212
00:10:42,800 --> 00:10:45,200
I really hate it when you
and your kids are fighting.

213
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,467
I'll go down now, okay?

214
00:10:51,567 --> 00:10:53,533
My dear, it's a good thing

215
00:10:53,667 --> 00:10:57,267
your older brother and sister
left early and didn't hear it.

216
00:10:58,400 --> 00:11:00,667
I feel sorry for dad.

217
00:11:01,900 --> 00:11:03,767
His wife is so cruel.

218
00:11:05,567 --> 00:11:07,433
That's what
I've been telling you.

219
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:09,900
Didn't I tell you to stop
calling your father?

220
00:11:11,033 --> 00:11:13,433
Because his wife is a demon.

221
00:11:13,567 --> 00:11:17,067
That's why your older brother
and sister tried to stop you

222
00:11:17,200 --> 00:11:18,967
from the start, because they
didn't want you to get hurt.

223
00:11:19,100 --> 00:11:20,867
Look at what happened now.

224
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:22,800
Because you kept disobeying us,

225
00:11:22,933 --> 00:11:26,333
now you've ended up hearing
all those hurtful words.

226
00:11:26,467 --> 00:11:29,533
Mom, I don't even care
about what she says.

227
00:11:29,667 --> 00:11:31,667
My concern is dad.

228
00:11:31,800 --> 00:11:33,667
I want to help him.

229
00:11:34,967 --> 00:11:35,833
What?

230
00:11:37,133 --> 00:11:38,333
How?

231
00:11:38,467 --> 00:11:40,300
Your dad is in Canada.

232
00:11:40,433 --> 00:11:41,900
How is that even possible, dear?

233
00:11:42,067 --> 00:11:44,000
Mom, I don't know, but...

234
00:11:44,133 --> 00:11:45,400
he needs me, Mom.

235
00:11:45,533 --> 00:11:50,500
He needs to know that someone
loves him and cares for him.

236
00:11:52,667 --> 00:11:54,133
Coleen....

237
00:11:54,267 --> 00:11:56,433
Jessica's there.

238
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:03,167
Mom, it's still different when
we're the ones who reach out.

239
00:12:04,367 --> 00:12:07,100
Dad needs to know that
he still has family here

240
00:12:07,233 --> 00:12:12,033
who cares about him,
even if it's just me, Mom.

241
00:12:12,167 --> 00:12:13,367
Coleen, no!

242
00:12:14,933 --> 00:12:17,933
This will be the last time
you call your father, okay?

243
00:12:29,067 --> 00:12:30,167
Sweetie.

244
00:12:31,300 --> 00:12:32,433
Stop crying.

245
00:12:34,133 --> 00:12:35,567
Stop crying now.

246
00:12:35,700 --> 00:12:38,467
Dear.

247
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:41,700
Let's not get involved in what's
happening with your father...

248
00:12:41,833 --> 00:12:43,967
and his family, okay?

249
00:12:45,367 --> 00:12:47,633
We're no longer part
of their problems.

250
00:12:50,167 --> 00:12:51,300
That's enough.

251
00:13:15,733 --> 00:13:16,700
Dear.

252
00:13:17,833 --> 00:13:20,767
Dear, don't think
about that anymore, okay?

253
00:13:20,900 --> 00:13:23,400
Daddy didn't feel
anything anyway.

254
00:13:23,567 --> 00:13:24,600
It's actually a good thing

255
00:13:24,733 --> 00:13:27,933
your mommy kicked me
on my paralyzed leg, see?

256
00:13:28,067 --> 00:13:29,700
I didn't get hurt.

257
00:13:31,167 --> 00:13:32,667
What's funny, Dad?

258
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,533
Mom still hurt you.

259
00:13:36,333 --> 00:13:38,233
Don't worry about me, okay?

260
00:13:40,600 --> 00:13:42,533
I'm worried about you.

261
00:13:44,267 --> 00:13:46,433
Your mom kicked you.

262
00:13:46,567 --> 00:13:47,633
Are you okay?

263
00:13:49,100 --> 00:13:50,600
I'm okay.

264
00:13:50,733 --> 00:13:53,267
You just got dragged
into her anger at me.

265
00:13:53,400 --> 00:13:55,100
Even Coleen.

266
00:13:55,267 --> 00:13:58,300
I'm sure she was hurt
by the things your mom said.

267
00:13:59,333 --> 00:14:01,700
If only I could call her...

268
00:14:01,833 --> 00:14:05,867
I'd like to check on her
and apologize.

269
00:14:07,400 --> 00:14:08,567
But...

270
00:14:10,033 --> 00:14:12,067
your phone is with your mom.

271
00:14:14,633 --> 00:14:15,867
Are you okay, dear?

272
00:14:18,300 --> 00:14:20,033
Mom's gone too far, Dad.

273
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:23,367
Living under one roof
with her...

274
00:14:23,500 --> 00:14:25,600
it's tearing us apart.

275
00:14:25,733 --> 00:14:28,833
Her abuse
is happening more often now.

276
00:14:30,433 --> 00:14:31,800
And I've had enough.

277
00:14:32,867 --> 00:14:34,067
I love her, Dad.

278
00:14:34,200 --> 00:14:35,333
I really do.

279
00:14:35,467 --> 00:14:38,100
But love doesn't mean
we have to endure this.

280
00:14:38,233 --> 00:14:40,167
Dad, let's leave her.

281
00:14:40,300 --> 00:14:42,767
Dad, let's go.

282
00:14:42,900 --> 00:14:45,367
Please, let's leave
for our own sake.

283
00:14:55,367 --> 00:14:59,700
Dear, no. We can't do that.

284
00:14:59,833 --> 00:15:03,000
She's your mom.
We can't leave her.

285
00:15:03,167 --> 00:15:04,733
Besides...

286
00:15:04,867 --> 00:15:06,600
where are we going?

287
00:15:06,733 --> 00:15:08,500
To the Philippines.

288
00:15:08,633 --> 00:15:12,100
Dear, we can't go home
to the Philippines.

289
00:15:12,233 --> 00:15:14,000
Dad, I'm already working on it.

290
00:15:14,133 --> 00:15:16,667
You don't deserve
this kind of treatment.

291
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:20,733
You have always protected me and
made sure I'm happy and safe.

292
00:15:20,867 --> 00:15:22,733
Now, it's my turn
to do the same.

293
00:15:22,867 --> 00:15:25,867
I'll make sure you'll be happy.
We'll be happy.

294
00:15:26,000 --> 00:15:27,367
Yes, dear. But...

295
00:15:27,500 --> 00:15:29,500
it's not that easy.

296
00:15:29,633 --> 00:15:31,833
Dad, I've decided.

297
00:15:31,967 --> 00:15:35,900
We don't know
what else mom will do to us.

298
00:15:36,067 --> 00:15:39,267
If something bad happens
to you because of her,

299
00:15:39,400 --> 00:15:41,967
I will never forgive myself.

300
00:15:42,100 --> 00:15:43,100
You know what, dear...

301
00:15:44,633 --> 00:15:46,900
I'm so lucky to have you, dear.

302
00:15:47,033 --> 00:15:48,900
Even with...

303
00:15:49,033 --> 00:15:51,333
all the mistakes
I've made in my life,

304
00:15:53,933 --> 00:15:57,367
God still gave me
a child like you.

305
00:15:57,500 --> 00:15:59,033
I'm even more blessed, Dad,

306
00:15:59,167 --> 00:16:02,533
because God gave you to me
to be my father.

307
00:16:11,867 --> 00:16:14,233
That Hazel is lucky
she's in Canada.

308
00:16:15,267 --> 00:16:16,567
If she were here, oh boy!

309
00:16:16,700 --> 00:16:18,333
What? You're going to confront
her, Sis?

310
00:16:18,467 --> 00:16:19,900
Oh, I'll even go with you!

311
00:16:20,033 --> 00:16:23,433
I'll help you yank
that witch's hair out!

312
00:16:23,567 --> 00:16:26,100
So, what did Jeff
and Andeng say?

313
00:16:27,867 --> 00:16:29,800
We couldn't tell either of them.

314
00:16:31,333 --> 00:16:34,100
I actually feel sorry
for Coleen.

315
00:16:34,233 --> 00:16:35,300
She needs...

316
00:16:35,433 --> 00:16:38,533
She needs comfort from
her older brother and sister...

317
00:16:38,667 --> 00:16:41,067
but we can't tell them anything.

318
00:16:41,200 --> 00:16:42,767
Because they're angry at Manuel.

319
00:16:43,833 --> 00:16:44,667
So...

320
00:16:44,800 --> 00:16:46,000
what now?

321
00:16:49,667 --> 00:16:50,467
How?

322
00:16:51,700 --> 00:16:53,967
I can't exactly
take Coleen's side either.

323
00:16:54,900 --> 00:16:55,900
Even though...

324
00:16:56,767 --> 00:17:00,633
even though I understand
her longing for her father,

325
00:17:01,700 --> 00:17:05,467
I also can't blame
Jeff and Andrea for being angry.

326
00:17:05,600 --> 00:17:07,200
Because...

327
00:17:07,333 --> 00:17:11,267
they felt that pain
when their father left them.

328
00:17:12,300 --> 00:17:13,733
It's hard, Sis.

329
00:17:13,867 --> 00:17:15,133
I feel torn between my children.

330
00:17:16,200 --> 00:17:17,467
What about Andeng?

331
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:19,900
Because out of your three kids,
she's the most sensitive

332
00:17:20,033 --> 00:17:23,667
when it comes to the issue
with their father.

333
00:17:23,800 --> 00:17:26,033
Didn't you two have an argument?

334
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:29,567
We're okay.

335
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:32,633
We have a silent agreement.

336
00:17:34,133 --> 00:17:36,700
No mention of Manuel,
no problem between us.

337
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:38,733
Especially when
it comes to work.

338
00:17:38,867 --> 00:17:40,867
No fights allowed.

339
00:17:42,133 --> 00:17:43,400
Sis...

340
00:17:44,533 --> 00:17:45,800
thank you.

341
00:17:47,133 --> 00:17:50,500
I always vent my feelings
to you.

342
00:17:51,567 --> 00:17:54,533
Oh, come on. That's nothing.
I understand, really.

343
00:17:55,533 --> 00:17:57,133
Well, it's your fault.

344
00:17:57,267 --> 00:17:58,967
You kicked Noah out.

345
00:17:59,100 --> 00:18:00,067
If you hadn't,

346
00:18:00,200 --> 00:18:04,067
you'd have someone else
to vent to right now.

347
00:18:09,167 --> 00:18:13,433
All right, let's go,
my<i> sisig</i> buddies!

348
00:18:13,567 --> 00:18:14,433
Is this it?

349
00:18:14,567 --> 00:18:16,867
Are all the products
we're bringing complete?

350
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,633
Please group them together,
okay?

351
00:18:18,767 --> 00:18:20,233
Stack them up.

352
00:18:20,367 --> 00:18:22,133
Your scarves.

353
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:24,333
Is that right? Is that complete?

354
00:18:24,467 --> 00:18:26,533
Okay, organize everything now,
okay?

355
00:18:26,667 --> 00:18:28,067
Group them together, please.

356
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:29,533
Now, go to your respective
groups.

357
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:32,667
As for the lists, Mom, Coleen,
Andrea, and I have them.

358
00:18:32,800 --> 00:18:35,100
Those are for the convenience
stores and markets

359
00:18:35,233 --> 00:18:36,600
your groups will be sampling at.

360
00:18:36,733 --> 00:18:37,700
Wait, this is wrong.

361
00:18:40,267 --> 00:18:41,600
Where's the rest of this?

362
00:18:43,133 --> 00:18:44,200
Put them together.

363
00:18:46,700 --> 00:18:48,333
<i>- You all know what to do, okay?
- This seems incomplete.</i>

364
00:18:52,067 --> 00:18:53,067
Felma.

365
00:18:54,100 --> 00:18:55,167
Felma, I'm sorry.

366
00:18:56,867 --> 00:18:58,767
I'm sorry for what happened
last time.

367
00:19:02,200 --> 00:19:03,133
It's okay.

368
00:19:04,167 --> 00:19:05,533
Let's forget about that.

369
00:19:06,700 --> 00:19:07,933
No, it's not okay.

370
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:11,733
I made a mistake.

371
00:19:13,900 --> 00:19:14,767
Can we talk?

372
00:19:17,633 --> 00:19:18,367
<i> Okay!</i>

373
00:19:18,500 --> 00:19:19,500
- Felma, please.
- That's all!

374
00:19:19,633 --> 00:19:20,733
<i> That's enough, guys.</i>

375
00:19:20,867 --> 00:19:23,333
And don't forget
the hairnets and gloves.

376
00:19:23,467 --> 00:19:25,733
Please be professional.

377
00:19:26,967 --> 00:19:28,900
- Mom.
- Uncle Noah.

378
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:31,800
Okay.

379
00:19:31,933 --> 00:19:33,100
We're ready?

380
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:34,300
- Game?
- Let's go,

381
00:19:34,433 --> 00:19:37,033
-<i> sisig</i> buddies!
- Okay, let's go,<i> sisig</i> buddies!

382
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:38,067
Let's go, let's go, let's go!

383
00:19:38,200 --> 00:19:39,567
- Come on, come on! Let's go!
- Okay.

384
00:19:42,667 --> 00:19:46,433
Yes. I'm leaving for Montreal.

385
00:19:46,567 --> 00:19:48,133
I know.

386
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,200
I'll attend a seminar there.

387
00:19:52,333 --> 00:19:57,200
Advanced Patient Care and
Critical Thinking in Nursing.

388
00:19:57,333 --> 00:19:58,267
What?

389
00:19:58,400 --> 00:20:00,333
You just started that job,
right?

390
00:20:00,467 --> 00:20:01,667
And you already have a seminar?

391
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,767
How come? The staff are busy,
they said.

392
00:20:03,933 --> 00:20:06,667
So, they sent us,
the newly hired ones.

393
00:20:06,800 --> 00:20:08,967
If only I didn't need this job.

394
00:20:09,100 --> 00:20:10,000
I have to go.

395
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,567
So...

396
00:20:14,700 --> 00:20:16,867
I guess you're happy.

397
00:20:17,000 --> 00:20:19,000
Because I'm leaving.

398
00:20:20,500 --> 00:20:23,800
Hazel, you're the only one
thinking that.

399
00:20:23,933 --> 00:20:25,633
Yeah, right.

400
00:20:25,767 --> 00:20:28,000
Your budget for three days
is in my vanity.

401
00:20:28,133 --> 00:20:29,433
Okay, Jessica?

402
00:20:29,567 --> 00:20:32,600
And please, behave.

403
00:20:34,300 --> 00:20:35,600
When I come back on Monday,

404
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:39,000
I want this house to be clean,
tidy, and smell nice.

405
00:20:39,133 --> 00:20:42,233
I don't want
a strong urine smell.

406
00:20:42,367 --> 00:20:43,700
Bye.

407
00:20:43,833 --> 00:20:44,933
I have to go.

408
00:20:47,633 --> 00:20:48,600
Jessica?

409
00:20:49,733 --> 00:20:51,900
- Lock the door.
- I will.

410
00:21:04,333 --> 00:21:05,967
Jessica, what are you doing?

411
00:21:18,233 --> 00:21:20,500
Wait, why do you have luggage?

412
00:21:20,633 --> 00:21:21,967
Are you leaving?

413
00:21:22,100 --> 00:21:23,167
Dad, let's go.

414
00:21:24,333 --> 00:21:25,333
Us?

415
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:26,367
Where are we going?

416
00:21:26,500 --> 00:21:27,933
Dad, now is the perfect time.

417
00:21:28,067 --> 00:21:30,400
We're escaping
while mom's not here.

418
00:21:40,367 --> 00:21:42,033
What happened was crazy, right?

419
00:21:42,200 --> 00:21:44,333
Our booth, the whole team,
got swarmed.

420
00:21:44,467 --> 00:21:46,367
In just one hour,
everything was sold out!

421
00:21:46,500 --> 00:21:47,367
Same with us!

422
00:21:47,500 --> 00:21:48,700
People were still asking
for more.

423
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:51,200
It's insane.<i> Sisig ni Bunso
</i>is seriously solid!

424
00:21:51,333 --> 00:21:53,833
They were all raving about
<i> Sisig ni Bunso</i> .

425
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:54,767
You guys were amazing!

426
00:21:54,900 --> 00:21:56,100
Give yourselves
a round of applause!

427
00:21:56,233 --> 00:21:58,000
Congratulations, guys!

428
00:21:58,133 --> 00:21:59,367
You did a great job.

429
00:21:59,500 --> 00:22:00,267
And because of that,

430
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,400
our youngest
is treating everyone

431
00:22:02,533 --> 00:22:04,400
to<i> pancit</i> and ice cream!

432
00:22:06,867 --> 00:22:09,700
All right then, let's go!
Time to celebrate!

433
00:22:09,833 --> 00:22:11,467
Thank you!

434
00:22:11,600 --> 00:22:13,033
- Thank you, Coleen!
- Congratulations!

435
00:22:13,167 --> 00:22:14,067
Thank you!

436
00:22:14,200 --> 00:22:16,133
Thank you, Coleen!

437
00:22:20,367 --> 00:22:21,367
Please.

438
00:22:22,733 --> 00:22:24,567
Stop avoiding me.

439
00:22:24,700 --> 00:22:25,700
Let's talk.

440
00:22:25,833 --> 00:22:26,667
Okay.

441
00:22:26,800 --> 00:22:27,733
Okay.

442
00:22:27,867 --> 00:22:30,167
Wait, I just need to listen
to our employees

443
00:22:30,300 --> 00:22:34,167
about the feedback
from the product sampling, okay?

444
00:22:34,300 --> 00:22:35,233
We will.

445
00:22:56,400 --> 00:22:59,667
Dad, didn't I make a promise
last time?

446
00:22:59,800 --> 00:23:02,600
I have actually started
working on it.

447
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:05,800
When I found out
about mom's conference,

448
00:23:05,933 --> 00:23:08,167
Mrs. Wilson and I
booked our flights.

449
00:23:08,300 --> 00:23:10,067
Everything's set.

450
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:12,633
Yes, but where will we live
when we get there?

451
00:23:12,767 --> 00:23:14,667
I found a cheap Airbnb.

452
00:23:14,800 --> 00:23:16,100
Dear.

453
00:23:16,233 --> 00:23:19,500
My savings aren't that much.
It'll run out quickly.

454
00:23:19,633 --> 00:23:21,067
Dad, don't worry.

455
00:23:21,200 --> 00:23:23,267
Mr. Wilson gave us some money.

456
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:25,833
Enough for us to start fresh
in Manila.

457
00:23:25,967 --> 00:23:26,900
Why did you accept it?

458
00:23:27,033 --> 00:23:29,267
It was already embarrassing
enough with them.

459
00:23:29,400 --> 00:23:31,267
Dad, they insisted.

460
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:33,433
I didn't really want
to accept it either.

461
00:23:33,567 --> 00:23:36,733
But they said we shouldn't
refuse it anymore,

462
00:23:36,867 --> 00:23:40,333
because they're the reason
this happened to you.

463
00:23:42,167 --> 00:23:43,900
But what about your studies?

464
00:23:44,033 --> 00:23:45,900
I already have
my school records.

465
00:23:46,033 --> 00:23:47,167
I can transfer there.

466
00:23:49,267 --> 00:23:50,733
Okay.

467
00:23:50,867 --> 00:23:51,833
But...

468
00:23:51,967 --> 00:23:53,900
Dad, trust me.

469
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,500
I got it, okay?

470
00:23:57,667 --> 00:24:00,167
We're finally going home.

471
00:24:00,300 --> 00:24:01,233
Let's go.

472
00:24:02,967 --> 00:24:04,067
Jessica?

473
00:24:05,467 --> 00:24:07,200
Jessica, open the door!

474
00:24:10,233 --> 00:24:11,233
Jessica?

475
00:24:12,667 --> 00:24:14,600
Jessica, open the door!

476
00:24:23,800 --> 00:24:25,467
Jessica, open the door.

477
00:24:25,600 --> 00:24:26,800
It's me.

478
00:24:36,833 --> 00:24:38,067
Jessica!

479
00:24:38,200 --> 00:24:39,533
What do we do, Dad?

480
00:24:45,433 --> 00:24:46,867
Jessica! What's wrong with you?

481
00:24:48,400 --> 00:24:50,167
I've been...

482
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,100
what's taking you so long?

483
00:24:52,233 --> 00:24:53,167
Jessica!

484
00:24:53,300 --> 00:24:54,367
Dad!

485
00:24:57,567 --> 00:24:58,633
What's wrong with these people?

486
00:25:04,500 --> 00:25:06,167
Jessica!

487
00:25:06,300 --> 00:25:07,267
Manuel!

488
00:25:12,667 --> 00:25:14,733
Just when I'm in a hurry!

489
00:25:14,867 --> 00:25:16,567
Why won't they open the door?

490
00:25:21,067 --> 00:25:22,067
So, Uncle?

491
00:25:22,200 --> 00:25:23,800
Is mom still avoiding you?

492
00:25:23,933 --> 00:25:27,433
Maybe I should just accept
that we're over.

493
00:25:27,567 --> 00:25:29,900
Jeff and I just got busy
because of<i> Sisig ni Bunso</i> .

494
00:25:30,033 --> 00:25:33,400
But now that everything's done,
we've got it covered.

495
00:25:33,533 --> 00:25:35,233
We'll talk to mom.

496
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:37,267
He's just a burden to you now,
isn't he?

497
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,633
You even considered
divorcing him?

498
00:25:40,767 --> 00:25:42,200
I changed my mind.

499
00:25:42,333 --> 00:25:43,567
He's still my husband.

500
00:25:43,700 --> 00:25:44,767
So he's mine.

501
00:25:44,900 --> 00:25:47,333
I already took out
an insurance policy on him.

502
00:25:47,467 --> 00:25:49,800
So if anyone should benefit
from that,

503
00:25:49,933 --> 00:25:51,300
it should be me.

504
00:25:51,433 --> 00:25:52,500
Just me.

505
00:25:52,633 --> 00:25:55,033
I want to call Jessica,

506
00:25:55,167 --> 00:25:57,567
just so I can find out
how dad's doing.

507
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,500
Are you still going to call,
Coleen?

508
00:25:59,633 --> 00:26:01,000
Mom already told you not to.

509
00:26:01,133 --> 00:26:02,100
I'm not a kid anymore

510
00:26:02,233 --> 00:26:04,833
for you to dictate
what I should and shouldn't do.

511
00:26:04,967 --> 00:26:07,800
Besides, I'm the only one who
wants to meet with dad, okay?

512
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:09,733
If you don't stop,
then just bear with me.

513
00:26:10,900 --> 00:26:12,933
But you'll lose your sister.
